In the era when the hero was born, 65 demons were sealed
into grimoires by humanity, but it was a time when the
terrifying seven demons were expanding their influence.

The oldest kingdom, Basileia, had fallen, faith in the gods
had waned, and humans who openly allied with demons began to
appear. These were the consequences brought about by the
failure of the three goddesses.

The three goddesses were fighting for the position of the
eldest daughter, but they completely lost their composure
and as a last resort, they made a certain choice.

Instead of sealing demons into grimoires, they chose to kill
them. And in order to do that, they created the role of the
hero.

The boy whose family was burned by a dragon was chosen by
it. However, the boy guided by the goddess Deirei still
knows nothing.

This is an irreversible action. It means that even the
ability to remain human will be lost.
